      "file_path": "feature-state-management/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/drools/statemanagement/DroolsPdpIntegrityMonitor.java",
      "patchset_number": 2,
      "line": 129,
      "message": "The idea was to avoid having to update a bunch of property files that were already configured to work with mariadb.  Nevertheless, I went ahead and updated the property files.\n\nNote: the property files already assume it's a mariadb, thus I just hard-coded the target-database to \"MySQL\" in the property files.  For the H2 DB used in junit tests, the value was set to \"Auto\" - apparently eclipselink is able to determine appropriate info about H2 by querying its metadata.",
